# Laturo Archaic & Obsolete Words (Oldlist)
# Words and forms that fell out of common use after 1900-2000s
# Includes archaic vocabulary, old accented variants, and historical terms

## Historical Note
# These words are preserved for historical texts, literature, and linguistic study
# Modern speakers typically do not use these in everyday conversation
# Some may still appear in formal, religious, or ceremonial contexts

## Archaic Pronouns & Forms (Pre-1900)
thú - thou (archaic singular "you", informal)
thúko - thy, thine (archaic possessive)
yé - ye (archaic plural "you")
yéko - your (archaic plural possessive)
methú - me (archaic first person)
wér - we (archaic, formal)
hím - him (archaic masculine)
hér - her (archaic feminine)
ít - it (archaic neutral)
thón - that one (archaic demonstrative)
thís - this one (archaic demonstrative)
whó - who (archaic interrogative)
whóm - whom (archaic interrogative object)
whóse - whose (archaic possessive interrogative)

