## Notes on Usage
# These archaic forms may still appear in:
# - Historical novels and period literature
# - Religious texts and ceremonies
# - Legal documents (some Latin-derived terms)
# - Poetry and formal verse
# - Academic historical writing
# - Museum descriptions and historical reenactments

# Modern Laturo speakers learning these forms do so primarily for:
# - Reading classical literature
# - Understanding historical documents
# - Academic research in linguistics
# - Cultural preservation
# - Theatrical and artistic purposes
